# Workflow

## Before implementing

1. For complex or multi-step tasks, use `.cursor/plans/` to draft a plan before coding
2. If any decision has multiple valid options, ask arbitrage questions first
3. If everything is obvious and unambiguous, proceed directly — no need to ask
4. When questions were asked, summarize choices and get confirmation before writing

## After implementing

1. Always re-read what was created
2. Update any documentation impacted by the changes (READMEs, ADR index, demo table...) — only what is affected, nothing extra
3. If a significant architectural or convention decision was made, create an ADR in `docs/decisions/` and update the index
4. Verify all project rules have been respected (structure, naming, style, etc.)
5. Present review findings: what's good, what's potentially wrong or inconsistent
6. If issues are found, propose fixes and ask for the user's decision
7. **If corrections were applied, re-read and review again** — repeat until no more issues are found
8. Only move on when the user confirms the result is satisfactory
